{{Infobox language |name=Thmon |states=[[Cambodia]] |speakers=? |date= |ref= |familycolor=Austro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Bahnaric languages|Bahnaric]] |fam3=Central |fam4=South |iso3=none |glotto=none }}
'''Thmon''' is a [[Bahnaric languages|Bahnaric]] language of northeastern Cambodia.
Kraol, Thmon, [[Khaonh language|Khaonh]], and [[Mel language|Mel]] all have about 70% lexical similarity with [[Stieng language|Stieng]], a Southern Bahnaric language (Barr & Pawley 2013:32).
The Thmon live in Memom village, [[Kaoh Nheaek District]], [[Mondulkiri Province]]. They had moved to Memom village from Benam village, Kotol commune, [[Sambour District]], [[Kratie Province]] in 1973 due to war (Barr & Pawley 2013:28).
==References== {{Reflist}} *Barr, Julie and Eric Pawley. 2013. ''[http://www.sil.org/resources/publications/entry/52517 Bahnaric Language Cluster survey of Mondul Kiri and Kratie Provinces, Cambodia]''. SIL International.
